20:
H-hey... H-how... do you... *pant*
even move that fast?
25:
Don't tell me you're out of energy
already, Mr. Flying Prince!
29:
Maintaining one's fitness is essential
to any self-respecting adventurer!
That's what my teacher taught me!
33:
Are you forgetting that I'm also a
modern high school student? 
I couldn't maintain a workout
schedule to save my life!
37:
Oh... You're hopeless. How about we
train together, then?
64:
Let go of me! I don't need some
stranger's help!
67: At least let us treat your woundsâ€”
70:
Go away! We've been fishing here
longer than you've been alive, you
tourist!
73:
What the hell... Show a little
gratitude, old man.
80: Argh! I can't stop thinking about it!
83:
He was still hurt, right? 
I wonder if he'll be okay?
87:
He said he didn't need help. 
I'd drop it.
92:
This area is being actively
developed... I imagine there are
certain circumstances at play that
we are not fully aware of.
96:
I mean... I don't think we should try to
push kindness onto other people.
99:
But still. There's gotta be something 
I can do to help!
104:
Yuna... You're kind of like an
overbearing mom sometimes, 
you know?
111:
I just want to be satisfied with this
situation and move on, or
something...
114:
...Yeah. It just doesn't feel right to
leave things like this.
118:
Yeah, all right! Thanks, everyone. 
I really appreciate the advice.
136:
Hey, could I get you guys to help me
with just one more thing?
145:
Oh! You're the man from earlier! Are
you feeling better now?
148:
...The monsters on the waters have
completely disappeared. Figure you
lot must be responsible.
152:
O-oh... Must have been... someone
else, haha...
159:
I never requested monster
extermination! Why are you paying
so much attention to me?
162: Because I just wanted to help!
165:
I couldn't stop worrying about your
situation, so I had to do something
about it!
169:
I really didn't care about your
stubborn protesting, to be honest!
177:
Th-this fish! It would sell for an
absolute fortune on the market!
185: If you don't want it, I'll throw it out.
188:
...Okay, I get the picture. Thank you,
Gramps!
191:
Hmph. This old man's not about to
be indebted to someone else.
194:
You know... I think you were actually
pretty happy to get our help, weren't
you?
197:
Wh-what? No! I wasn't happy in the
slightest!
200:
Yeah, yeah. If you ever find yourself
in trouble again, just let us know!
Okay?
